text: The Division of St George was an Australian Electoral Division for the Australian House of Representatives in the state of New South Wales. The division was created in 1949. It was abolished in 1993. It was named for the suburb of St George. It was located in the suburbs of Hurstville, Rockdale and Arncliffe. The Division of Watson replaced it when it was abolished. ==Members== Member Party Term Bill Graham Liberal 1949–1954 Nelson Lemmon Labor 1954–1955 Bill Graham Liberal 1955–1958 Lionel Clay Labor 1958–1963 Leonard Bosman Liberal 1963–1969 Bill Morrison Labor 1969–1975 Maurice Neil Liberal 1975–1980 Bill Morrison Labor 1980–1984 Stephen Dubois Labor 1984–1993 St George Category:1949 establishments in Australia Category:1993 disestablishments in Australia
title: Division of St George
